HEADWORD: Melopœia
<hw>Mel`o*p⟦oe⟧"ia</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/; <grk>me`los</grk> song + <grk>poiei^n</grk> to make.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The art of forming melody; melody; -- now often
used for a melodic passage, rather than a complete melody.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

